# Define the Auto-Apply Surface

## Step

Gardener-style direct is granted — but exactly which files may the retro
change without a human gate? Candidates: public-openers.txt, GREETING_FLAVORS,
persona instruction text blocks, tool docstrings, public-context.md /
shitrat-brain pages (already gardened), config knobs (endpointing delays?).
And what's the receipt shape (commit message contract, Bugle mention, revert
path)? Resolved when an explicit allowlist + receipt contract is written.

## Result (2026-07-13)

Resolved as the project's autonomy charter: **[infra/voice-agent/VISION.md](../../../infra/voice-agent/VISION.md)** —
Joel's framing: it DEFINES what automation does autonomously and where he's in
the loop. Gist: auto-apply = openers + greeting flavors + tool docstrings/
result-headers only; persona, config knobs, models, tools, carrier, spend all
gated; quarantine/disclosure/allowlist forbidden forever. Receipts: one
retro(auto) commit per tuning + a Bugle "Tuning receipts" item. Guardrails:
compile + banned-grep + max two tunings per retro + post-apply synthetic call
with auto-revert. Promotion ladder: ten clean applies + sign-off up, any
revert demotes. Intelligence may escalate to pi with gpt-5.6-rol:xhigh when
warranted — logged, and never escalating authority.
